ear of God, imagining that they are to live for ever, and that it is they who have to inherit the world: it shows the greatest ignorance possible, to think, in spite of experience, that there is no need of faith; but perhaps some men actually exist in Italy who are of this opinion! ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"56e02f58-ebf8-4f23-97e9-b7ba943541b6","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":1,"value":"f219551f-c528-4666-8ada-4b95b7476b58","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7311766c-c162-4806-aaeb-227615880e7b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":44,"end":48,"value":"9c715d50-cacd-45b8-9295-ba4feef986f7","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"866bb185-90f1-4b58-9be1-9943758177c1","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":60,"end":67,"value":"8a3f914d-b8ad-4bc9-9313-662b113d9878","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"2523ab65-c09c-4818-b791-adac448c1953","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":114,"end":126,"value":"f96d2432-2bbb-4559-8c79-614d9fdbd33d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"f2b5571c-00a1-433b-81ff-10a4a0e82765","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":157,"end":164,"value":"fad6a621-6670-4b2e-b4e9-ab5d08743422","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c30f19cc-408f-4021-b243-393d98cba67a","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":252,"end":254,"value":"a3fed3ec-1814-4027-a2d5-ac598b2fcb6f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"30a028ba-8c8a-4c2a-98d7-792cc52dd64c","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":343,"end":347,"value":"ad8f0e91-012b-46ec-a273-96681d7d2c18","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"dfe43f1a-7999-4372-9075-a293be205e12","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":497,"end":501,"value":"ca7c8738-7589-4dea-816b-06b3bb1cb449","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"cff05a12-4997-4d23-9e95-21efb021294c","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"We heard that the Pope had arrested Cardinal Orsini and the Bishop of Florence, who is also an Orsini. ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"3c701683-0aeb-4ed0-bbb9-a079